1. Pre requisites ::
   ==============
   stanford-parser (Version 2.0.1 or latter)
   Download http://nlp.stanford.edu/software/lex-parser.shtml
   bison
   clips
   flex
   java (version: 1.6 or above)

2. Set the path for Java in .bashrc/.bash_profile 
	export PATH= path for java
         Ex:   export PATH=$HOME/jdk1.6.0_03/bin:$PATH

3. Set the path for Stanford parser in .bashrc/.bash_profile
        export STANFORD_PATH=path for stanford parser

        Ex: export STANFORD_PATH=$HOME/stanford-parser-full-2013-06-20

4. Source bashrc 
         source ~/.bashrc

 Note: This version handles only one sentence at a time. A sample input file named "test" is provided with this package. 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To view Derived Tree, Derivation Tree & Dependecy Tree ::
=========================================================

Inside tree_viewer directory :: 
----------------------------

1. Compile programmes:
 
         bash compile.sh

2. Run view_trees.sh:
         bash view_trees.sh <input-file>
           Ex:  bash view_trees.sh test
  
  Two windows would open
         i)  Constituency Tree Viewer ---> For viewing derived tree and derivation tree. 
         ii) Dependency Tree Viewer   ---> For viewing dependency tree.
 
         Steps to view trees:
 	  Go to File menu -> select Open Treebank
 	  (A new window opens)  --> select the path upto working directory and then 
	 		   	   a.  select <input-file>_derived_tree file and Click Open
                                         Ex: test_derived_tree 
                                   b.  select <input-file>_derivation_tree file and Click Open
                                         Ex: test_derivation_tree
		                   c.  select <input-file>_dependency_tree and Click Open
                                         Ex: test_dependency_tree 

  Note: To remove out files, run: bash remove-out-files.sh
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To view Dependency Tree in paninian format::
=========================================
Pre requisites:
--------------
1. anu_testing software need to be installed successfully 
2. Run Anusaaraka_stanford.sh <file-name>
	Ex: Anusaaraka_stanford.sh sample
3. bash dependency_in_paninian_format.sh <file-name> <sentence-number>
	Ex: dependency_in_paninian_format.sh sample 2.1

   Dependency Tree Viewer opens
	 Steps to view trees:
          Go to File menu -> select Open Treebank
          (A new window opens)  --> select the path upto working directory and then
					-> select paninian_to_conllx_format.dat and Click Open
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
